  &lt;p id="EIUyre"&gt;Massachusetts Gov. Charlie Baker has refused to sign a law banning most government use of facial recognition. &lt;a href="https://www.bostonglobe.com/2020/12/10/metro/baker-sends-police-bill-back-legislature-asking-changes/"&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Boston Globe&lt;/em&gt; reported&lt;/a&gt; last week that Baker sent an omnibus police reform bill back to state lawmakers, asking for changes that included striking the facial recognition rules.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="cRC0cT"&gt;Massachusetts legislators &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2020/12/2/22094902/massachusetts-facial-recognition-ban-bill-vote-passed-police-reform"&gt;passed the first&lt;/a&gt; major state-level facial recognition ban, following a model set by individual cities like Boston and San Francisco. &lt;a href="https://malegislature.gov/Bills/191/S2963?=11302020"&gt;The bill&lt;/a&gt; says public agencies, including police departments, can’t use or acquire biometric surveillance systems. It makes exceptions for running facial recognition searches against a motor vehicles registration database, as long as police obtain a warrant or demonstrate “immediate danger” that...&lt;/p&gt;
